T001.initial_thoughts: The user wants a comprehensive SIP plan for retirement. I need to follow these steps: 1. Normalize the inputs (goal, target, horizon, risk). 2. Adjust the target amount for inflation over 30 years. 3. Calculate the required monthly SIP based on the inflation-adjusted target, using the return rate corresponding to a 'high' risk appetite (12% per annum). 4. Define the asset allocation plan for a 'high' risk profile (70% equity, 30% debt) and list appropriate fund categories. 5. Generate a full, month-by-month projection table for the entire 30-year (360-month) period using the mandatory compound interest algorithm. I will ensure all calculations are accurate and all outputs conform to the strict JSON schema.
